--Positive prompt with wildcards will show preview txt in "Wildcards Preview". Still works with normal prompts as well. 


--VAE switch used to switch between baked (built in) or optional VAE.


--Use Process Switch to swap between txt2img, img2img, inpainting or controlnets.


--img2img and inpainting, will keep keep aspect ratio of loaded image. If you want to use a different ratio change "img Downscale" node to "imagescale" node. 


--If using control net while switch is set to "txt2img" it will use the "Easy Aspect Ratio". When set to control net it will keep the ratio of the loaded image. 


--Right click loaded image to load in mask editor for inpainting.


--Disable UHD Upscale Model with CTRL+M if you do not want 4k upscaled image. 


--Save HD Img is 2 x Original size, Save UHD Img is 4 x Original size
Recommend using 2x upscaler for UHD image.

ENJOY!

DO NOT MUTE "Apply ControlNet", just use bypass as the conditioning runs through here. 

Pink indicates the node is bypassed. 
Transparent indicates the node is muted.

Updated CNet Switch so now it doesn't require inputs so you can mute the other nodes [OpenPose, Depth, Canny or Normal] when using the CNet work flow. 

Mute/Disable: CNTRL+M
Bypass: CNTRL+B
